Therefore, we recommended that the management to do the following to enhance utilization of the 20% Development Fund:
For the City Planning and Development Coordinator to:
• Closely monitor the utilization and implementation of priority projects for the attainment of desirable socio-economic development and environmental management outcomes and to maximize the usage of the fund;
• Recommend to the Local Development Council to reprogram savings out of the completed projects (both from continuing and current appropriation);
• Evaluate projects before presentation to the Local Development Council to minimize number of abandoned projects.
For the Concerned Implementing Office on proposed PPAs to:
• Coordinate with the City Engineering office and ensure that program of works, project designs, detailed estimates, coordination with other agencies and other needed documents needing approval had been prepared and approved without objections prior to its inclusion to the Annual Investment Plan;
• Fast track the implementation based on the scheduled time frames indicated in the AIP to achieve the desired management outcomes

