b) Discontinue the practice of charging against the SEF, the payment of salaries, allowances and other benefits of clerks, administrative aides, laborer and security guards who are employed as casual employees of the City, regardless of their place of assignments to various public school. Such expenses are chargeable to the general fund of the City subject to existing auditing rules and regulations; and
c) Henceforth, restrict the allocation and prioritization of the SEF to the programs and projects specifically defined under the afore-stated law, rules and regulations in order to minimize the benefits that the public elementary and secondary schools could derive from this fund.

